		<td><b>Re: Colour $0D and emphasis bits glitches on TV</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Someone should convert the voltage levels on <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NTSC_video" class="postlink">NTSC video</a> to IRE units so that analog video geeks can make better sense of it.<br /></div>Depends on whether anything's doing any normalization, as well as what exactly the output looks like into a 75Î© and/or infinite load.<br /><br />Fortunately, for receiving over RF (which should be normalized), we can derive it from the existing data.<br /><br />So there's at least 3 different values we'll need to calculate.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
